The two [Purple Pink stones at 0.70ct](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-20891050?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($15,403–$16,803) demonstrate the Brownish Purple Pink vs. Brownish Purplish Pink distinction — "Purple Pink" indicates purple as a near-equal secondary hue, commanding slightly less than pure Purplish Pink. In white gold, both read as raspberry-pink with violet undertones — one of the most dramatic natural color combinations available in a pear diamond.

