## Which Pear Settings Amplify Pink Diamond Color Best

Pink diamonds interact with setting metalwork differently than colorless diamonds. The primary goal is color amplification — maximizing the perceived saturation of the pink center stone through metal reflection, contrast geometry, and surrounding diamond interaction.

### Halo Settings: Maximum Pink Amplification

Halo settings create the strongest color amplification effect for pink pear diamonds. White diamonds surrounding a pink center stone create a contrast boundary that makes the pink read more saturated — the eye perceives the pink as more intense against the surrounding colorless halo than in isolation. This effect is most pronounced in white gold settings where the cool metal and white halos create maximum contrast.

