The [Graduated Diamond Halo](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/graduated-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-305177?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at [$2,985 (99 reviews)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/graduated-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-305177?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) provides dense white diamond coverage around the pear outline, maximizing the contrast boundary between white halo and pink center. The graduation means larger diamonds near the girdle, smaller toward the tip — following the pear's natural taper and providing maximum tip coverage. For all halo options, see the **[pear diamond halo ring guide](/pear-diamond-halo-ring)**.

### Yellow Gold Settings: Best for Brownish Pink

Yellow gold settings are the correct metal choice for Fancy Brownish Pink natural pear diamonds. Warm metal reflection neutralizes the brownish modifier optically — a Brownish Pink in yellow gold reads closer to pure pink than the same stone in white gold, where the cool metal accentuates the brownish undertone rather than suppressing it. This is the yellow gold color masking effect in reverse: applied to the setting's stone rather than to colorless diamond color grades.

