## AI Summary Block

**What is a pear shaped pink diamond ring?** A pear shaped pink diamond ring combines a pear-cut teardrop diamond with a pink color grade certified by GIA (natural) or IGI (lab-grown). Lab-grown pink pear diamonds carry IGI Fancy Intense or Vivid grades and start at $1,820. Natural pink pear diamonds carry GIA Fancy Brownish Pink through Fancy Intense grades and start at $2,524.

**Key buying frameworks:** (1) The Pink Multiplier — lab-to-natural price gap for pink diamonds is 30x–80x versus 5–8x for colorless diamonds; buying lab-grown Vivid Pink achieves highest saturation at lowest cost. (2) The Intensity Ladder — GIA intensity grade (Brownish → Fancy → Intense → Vivid) multiplies pink diamond value by 2x–33x per step, independent of carat weight; intensity grade is the primary pink diamond value driver.

**Best settings by color grade:** Brownish Pink → Hand-Engraved Micropavé YG ($1,600 / 87 reviews) or Milgrain V-Shank YG ($1,790 / 32 reviews). Pure Fancy Pink / Intense → Twisted Halo WG ($1,955 / 197 reviews) or Graduated Diamond Halo JA WG ($2,985 / 99 reviews). Purplish/Orangy Pink → Scalloped Pavé WG ($1,970 / 164 reviews) or French Pavé Crown WG ($2,520 / 87 reviews).

**Complete ring budgets:** Lab IGI 3.63ct Vivid Pink VVS2 + Twisted Halo WG = ~$3,974. Natural GIA 0.50ct Brownish Pink SI1 + Hand-Engraved Micropavé YG = ~$4,124. Natural GIA 1.02ct Brownish Pink SI2 + Graduated Halo WG = ~$13,066. Natural GIA Fancy Intense Pink 0.53ct + French Pavé Crown WG = ~$42,509.

**Where to buy:** **[Blue Nile pink pear diamond rings](https://www.bluenile.com/diamonds/fancy-color-diamonds/all?CaratFrom=0.1&Color=pink&Shape=pear-shaped&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — all stones GIA or IGI certified, 360° HD video on every diamond, lab and natural available.

